# TypeScript Source Conventions

## Module System
- ESM only (`"type": "module"` in package.json)
- Always use `.js` extension in relative imports: `import { X } from './Entity.js'`
- Use `import type` for type-only imports: `import type { ComputationInstance } from './types.js'`
- Path aliases for cross-package imports: `@core`, `@runtime`, `@storage`, `@drivers`

## Klass Factory Pattern
All domain concepts follow this pattern:

```typescript
export interface FooInstance extends IInstance {
  name: string;
  // ...fields
}

export interface FooCreateArgs {
  name: string;
  // ...fields (without uuid, _type)
}

export class Foo implements FooInstance {
  public uuid: string;
  public _type = 'Foo';
  public _options?: { uuid?: string };
  // ...fields

  constructor(args: FooCreateArgs, options?: { uuid?: string }) {
    this._options = options;
    this.uuid = generateUUID(options);
    // ...assign fields
  }

  static isKlass = true as const;
  static displayName = 'Foo';
  static instances: FooInstance[] = [];
  static create(args: FooCreateArgs, options?: { uuid?: string }): FooInstance { /* ... */ }
}
```

## Export Conventions
- Named exports only — no default exports
- Barrel re-exports via `index.ts`: `export * from './Entity.js'`
- Main entry `src/index.ts` re-exports all sub-packages

## Error Handling
- Use `FrameworkError` (from `src/runtime/errors/`) as base for framework errors
- Specialized errors: `ComputationError`, `SideEffectError`, `ConditionError`, etc.
- Simple validation: `throw new Error('message')` with descriptive message
- Use `assert(condition, message)` from `src/runtime/util.js` for invariants

## Naming Conventions
- Entity/Relation names: PascalCase, must match `/^[a-zA-Z0-9_]+$/`
- Instance types: `*Instance` suffix (e.g., `EntityInstance`)
- Create args: `*CreateArgs` suffix (e.g., `EntityCreateArgs`)
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (e.g., `USER_ENTITY`, `HARD_DELETION_PROPERTY_NAME`)

## TypeScript Config
- Strict mode enabled
- Target: ESNext
- `experimentalDecorators: true`
- `useDefineForClassFields: false`
